The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, July 10, 2004 				 Wheels crush, mob blazes
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Bongaon (North 24-Parganas), July 9: Two school students were run over here this afternoon and a mob tried to avenge the deaths by burning at least 10 other vehicles. 																								Rakesh Biswas and Moloy Roy, both 13 and Class V students at Kesablal Vidyamandir, were hit by a truck on Station Road, about 70 km from Calcutta, on their way back home. 																								As news of the deaths spread, about 500 people converged on the spot. Some chased down the killer truck. The driver fled as a torching frenzy was sparked off.																								Traffic on the road that leads to the Petrapole checkpost on the Bangladesh border was stuck for about three hours.
